                            <comment id="14295400" author="stack" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 17:06:27 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Resolving as invalid. Looks like an HTRACE issue, not an hbase one &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=giacomotaylor&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;giacomotaylor&quot;&gt;James Taylor&lt;/a&gt; (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTRACE-92&quot; title=&quot;Thread local storing the currentSpan is never cleared&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HTRACE-92&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HTRACE-92&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14295417" author="jamestaylor" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 17:21:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;My thinking was that HTrace is not going to know when to reset the thread local state through Tracer.getInstance().continueSpan(null), while a client (HBase in this case) would. Is that not the case, &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=stack&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;stack&quot;&gt;stack&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14295449" author="stack" created="Wed, 28 Jan 2015 17:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=giacomotaylor&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;giacomotaylor&quot;&gt;James Taylor&lt;/a&gt; HTrace is guest of the hbase process. If it expects the host to do resets on it on a period, it is a bad &apos;guest&apos;. Lets try fix over in HTRACE w/o having to have hbase or hdfs or phoenix or whoever have to reach into HTRACE implementation detail to do null-sets.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
